  <yourItinerary><![CDATA[<p><strong>DAY 1</strong></p>
<p>Meet you Inghams Santa Breaks Reps at Kittilä airport and transfer from the airport by coach to your accommodation. Once you arrive settle in to your accommodation, pick up your suits and boots and familiarise yourself with the resort. </p>
<p><strong>DAY 2 </strong></p>
<p>A full day of activities including</p>
<ul>
<li>An unforgettable reindeer farm visit and reindeer sled ride. Meet Rudolph's friends at this 100 year old Lappish farm and enjoy the wonder of a tranquil reindeer sleigh ride in the forest</li>
<li>Christmas Baking and Crafts. Bake traditional Finnish gingerbread cookies and make your own Christmas decorations to take home as a memory of your stay in Lapland</li>
<li>Lunch in a traditional Lappish kota</li>
<li>Meeting with Santa. The local friendly elves know the secret path to Santa's hideaway cabin where each family has a private meeting with Santa</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Day 3</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Husky sled ride. Meet the excited huskies for a 6km safari. A chance for adults to drive the husky sled whilst small children travel with the guide's sled</li>
<li>Snow fun winter activities. test your skills at cross-country skiing, tobogganing and other fun snow activities. There is even a mini snowmobile ride for children where they can drive themselves</li>
<li>Lunchtime buffet</li>
<li>Snowmobile safari, discovering the beautiful landscape of Lapland. Two adults share a snowmobile with children travelling in a sleigh</li>
<li>Christmas Dinner - a buffet of different foods and traditional Finnish Christmas dishes</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Day 4</strong></p>
<p>After a magical few days, it’s time to say goodbye to your new friends before being transferred by coach to the airport for your flight home.</p>
<p>If you are staying on a 3 night (4 day) stay then the snowmobile and Christmas dinner are on Day 4 and departures on Day 5.</p>
<p><em>Please note the above itinerary may vary and other activities may also be available locally.</em></p>
<p>This is a full itinerary but additional optional extras are available to book through the hotel reception the day before the activity takes place. Optional excursions can include Aurora snowmobiling, cross country skiing and snowshoe rental. These excursions are payable locally. </p>
<p><em>Please note</em></p>
<p><em><strong>Husky Safari:</strong><span> </span>Times and distances are approximate and may vary due to weather conditions. All children under 12 years must be driven by a guide (5-6 children per guide sleigh). Adults (aged 18+) drive their own sleigh, with 1 - 2 adults (aged 12+) in the sleigh. </em></p>
<p><em><strong>Reindeer Safari: </strong>Times and distances are approximate and may vary due to weather conditions. </em></p>
<p><em><strong>Snowmobile Safaris:</strong><span> </span>Times and distances are approximate and may vary due to weather conditions. Children age 4-14 yrs and will be towed behind the guide in a sleigh or pod.<span> </span><span>Children must be aged 15 yrs or above </span><strong>and</strong><span> at least 140cm tall to ride as a passenger on a snowmobile. </span>Snowmobile drivers must be 18yrs and bring a<span> </span><strong>full, photographic driver's licence</strong><span> </span>with them. Snowmobiles are shared as standard. Guests wishing to upgrade to a single riders can do so at reception on arrival (payable locally). Some customers may need to upgrade locally to a single driving snowmobile (payable locally), if sharing a snowmobile is not possible in their group. </em></p>
<p><em>Travel insurance is a condition of booking with us, and you should ensure that your chosen policy covers the activities that you plan to take part in during your holiday. Your policy should provide cover for your own personal and medical expenses, however individual policies will not cover damage to snowmobiles or skidoos and a compulsory excess will be payable directly to the supplier of the snowmobile/skidoo excursion.</em></p>
<p> </p>]]></yourItinerary>
